From the previous hint, we can conclude that we can decrease the number of changes by at most $$$2$$$. For us to be able to decrease the number of changes by $$$2$$$, it shall hold that $$$s_{l-1} 
eq s_l$$$ and $$$s_r 
eq s_{r+1}$$$.
If we want to decrease the number of changes by $$$1$$$, it is enough to make $$$s_{l-1} 
eq s_l$$$ and to make $$$r=n$$$.
If we cannot do either of the previous two, the number of changes cannot be decreased.
